32:12.500 --> 32:16.510
Still,your name is on it,so--
so thank you for the travel bag.

32:16.520 --> 32:18.970
Believe it or not,I'm
actually using it right now.

32:18.980 --> 32:21.040
I'm,uh,I'm heading off
to rome on business.

32:21.080 --> 32:25.050
So,um...bye.

32:30.790 --> 32:33.220
come on,maggie,pick up.

32:33.780 --> 32:35.980
My cell died.

32:35.990 --> 32:37.830
We'll get you a new one in italy.

32:37.840 --> 32:41.370
So you'll be incommunicado
for a couple days.

32:43.120 --> 32:44.950
Are you all right?

32:44.960 --> 32:47.730
Yeah. Yeah,I'm great.

32:51.020 --> 32:55.330
This is the final boarding
call for keystar flight 524,

32:55.340 --> 33:00.840
nonstop service to rome,now
boarding at gate 17.

33:13.320 --> 33:15.760
somebody
call 9-1-1!

33:33.500 --> 33:35.520
Hey,maggie.

33:35.530 --> 33:36.540
How you feeling?

33:36.550 --> 33:39.930
Uh,like I stopped the
express train with my head.

33:39.940 --> 33:41.120
I'm gonna go tell a
doctor,tell them you're awake.

33:41.130 --> 33:48.380
Wait,wait. Um,did what
I think happened happen?

33:48.980 --> 33:52.550
Your aneurysm burst,eli--
one of them,anyway.

33:52.560 --> 33:56.190
The doctors managed to stop the
bleeding with some kind of...coils?

33:56.200 --> 33:58.000
Endovascular coiling.

33:58.010 --> 33:59.690
You remember?

34:01.250 --> 34:03.790
Did you tell the paramedics
I had an aneurysm?

34:03.800 --> 34:08.080
Yeah. They thought
you had a heart attack.

34:08.090 --> 34:10.600
Lucky I was there.

34:10.610 --> 34:13.880
I was on my way to save you.

34:13.889 --> 34:17.060
Thanks for being late
to get on the plane.

34:18.989 --> 34:22.739
I did get on...with paul.

34:22.750 --> 34:25.100
But it didn't feel right.

34:25.110 --> 34:27.860
Maybe you're not the only one
who gets messages sometimes.

34:27.870 --> 34:30.170
Maybe.

34:31.060 --> 34:34.230
What happened with the plane?

34:34.239 --> 34:37.170
How many people died?

34:37.179 --> 34:39.270
None of them,eli.

34:39.280 --> 34:43.889
When I insisted on getting off,it was a
big deal because they were ready to go.

34:43.900 --> 34:46.440
The pilots had to start all over.

34:46.449 --> 34:49.280
They ran another safety
check,and this time they--

34:49.290 --> 34:50.600
they found what was
wrong with the plane.

34:50.610 --> 34:54.870
A problem with the engine--
fuel pump or something.

34:54.880 --> 34:57.070
They said that it would
have blown up in the air.

34:57.080 --> 34:59.020
So you saved everybody.

34:59.030 --> 35:03.520
I think in our way,we...we both did.

35:05.300 --> 35:08.250
What's going on here,eli?

35:08.260 --> 35:10.540
You mean with us?

35:14.330 --> 35:15.260
He's awake.

35:15.270 --> 35:18.150
Yeah. One aneurysm down,one to go.

35:18.190 --> 35:20.540
- You know,I owe you a big,fat I-told-you-so. 
- Yeah,I know.

35:20.550 --> 35:21.490
You could've wound up a vegetable,

35:21.530 --> 35:26.850
which,apart from kicking your I.Q.Up a
few points,wouldn't have been very good.

35:26.880 --> 35:27.980
You've got this one to thank.

35:28.020 --> 35:30.170
And I can't imagine the way she's
gonna hold that over my head.

35:30.210 --> 35:31.760
Oh,I've got a list.

35:31.770 --> 35:33.330
yeah.

35:34.980 --> 35:37.310
So,um,it's okay.

35:37.320 --> 35:39.900
The plane was grounded.

35:40.250 --> 35:42.370
Happy ending.

35:44.070 --> 35:46.060
What?

35:46.070 --> 35:47.920
It's diane.

35:47.930 --> 35:50.270
She went into surgery,and
we performed the transplant,

35:50.280 --> 35:53.600
and we were taking her
to the I.C.U.When...

35:55.210 --> 35:57.500
when she threw an embolism.

35:57.510 --> 35:59.660
No.

35:59.670 --> 36:02.470
I'm so sorry,eli.

36:02.480 --> 36:03.140
That's not fair.

36:03.150 --> 36:07.000
You did everything you could. You
could not have seen this coming.

36:13.320 --> 36:15.110
it's diane's surgeon.

36:15.120 --> 36:17.310
Her,uh,her mother's here.

36:17.320 --> 36:21.910
And,well,the heart's still viable.

36:30.180 --> 36:32.450
You gonna be okay?

36:32.460 --> 36:34.200
I don't know.

37:29.470 --> 37:32.920
it seems like such a
long time ago,doesn't it?

37:35.970 --> 37:37.670
It's beautiful.

37:41.550 --> 37:43.730
Is this heaven?

37:44.190 --> 37:45.560
Am I dead?

37:45.600 --> 37:48.310
It's the panch chuli peaks.

37:48.340 --> 37:50.510
I thought you'd recognize them.

37:50.840 --> 37:53.590
Could be heaven,though.

37:53.640 --> 37:56.320
Just as beautiful.

37:56.560 --> 37:59.440
Always wanted to see them.

37:59.480 --> 38:02.030
Are you my dad or...

38:02.050 --> 38:04.180
god?

38:04.960 --> 38:08.800
It's complicated.

38:08.840 --> 38:11.380
Don't push too hard against that.

38:16.260 --> 38:18.850
Well,I missed you.

38:18.890 --> 38:22.450
You've done well for
yourself,eli,both you and nate.

38:22.490 --> 38:24.490
No father could be prouder.

38:24.520 --> 38:27.280
And I know how hard it's been.

38:27.320 --> 38:28.690
I know you get
angry sometimes--

38:28.730 --> 38:30.690
like now.

38:32.430 --> 38:34.090
Diane wasn't supposed to die.

38:34.120 --> 38:35.950
Says you.

38:35.990 --> 38:37.720
You don't know.

38:37.760 --> 38:39.330
You're not god,eli.

38:39.360 --> 38:44.430
I broke my promise to diane,and I-I might've
destroyed that girl's family for nothing.

38:44.470 --> 38:49.370
Not for nothing. For grace.

38:49.410 --> 38:50.640
- Grace?
- Grace.

38:50.680 --> 38:52.850
- The--the person? 
- Grace. She's in san francisco.

38:52.900 --> 38:57.480
She was waiting for the right time to
reconnect with you,eli,and then she...

38:58.390 --> 39:00.760
Her heart gave out.

39:00.790 --> 39:06.670
She needed a transplant,and as it
turns out,there was a viable heart.

39:10.290 --> 39:13.570
It was for your soul mate.

39:13.970 --> 39:16.620
Mysterious ways,and yours
is not to reason why.

39:16.650 --> 39:21.350
W--yes,it
is.

39:22.600 --> 39:24.140
I am happy for grace.

39:24.170 --> 39:27.330
I'm happy,and I'm thankful.

39:27.370 --> 39:32.030
But if you or god or whatever,you
want me to keep doing this,

39:32.080 --> 39:41.250
it has to be my way,especially when people that
I love--people like maggie-- are on the line.

39:41.290 --> 39:44.890
And by the way,just cut that crap out.

39:48.970 --> 39:52.090
people wonder why god
gave man free will.

39:53.760 --> 39:58.270
and don't think I didn't notice how
you said you love maggie just now.

40:05.350 --> 40:07.790
Was this a test?

40:10.770 --> 40:13.620
Everything's a test.

40:13.650 --> 40:16.610
Life is a test.

40:16.650 --> 40:18.620
And you...

40:19.720 --> 40:24.920
you,my boy,you're passing
with flying colors.

40:26.100 --> 40:28.530
I couldn't be more proud.

40:28.560 --> 40:37.980
* Some kind of magic
happens late at night *

40:39.480 --> 40:44.300
* when the moon smiles down at me *

40:44.890 --> 40:48.890
* bathes me in its light *

40:50.170 --> 40:54.930
* I fell asleep beneath you *

40:56.110 --> 41:00.840
* in the tall blades of grass *

41:01.660 --> 41:07.160
* when I woke the world was new *

41:07.190 --> 41:11.500
* I never had to ask *

41:13.020 --> 41:16.670
* it's a brand new day *

41:16.720 --> 41:18.650
* the sun is shining *

41:18.680 --> 41:22.820
* it's a brand new day *

41:23.750 --> 41:32.580
* for the first time in such
a long, long time I know *

41:34.750 --> 41:38.140
* i'll be okay *
